# BFA Site Audit Report

> Complete code-level review of every major page and component.

---

## 🔴 Critical Bugs (will break functionality)

### 1. Contact Form — Submit Does Nothing
**File:** [Contact.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/pages/Contact.tsx#L60)

The contact form has `onSubmit={(e) => e.preventDefault()}` — it just blocks the default browser action and does nothing. No data is sent, no success message shown, no toast, nothing. **Users will think it's broken.**

**Fix:** Wire it to an email API (e.g. EmailJS, Formspree, or Supabase Edge Function) and show a success state.

---

### 2. Admissions Form — Unused `e` Catch Parameter
**File:** [Admissions.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/pages/Admissions.tsx#L64)

```tsx
} catch (e: any) {
  setError(e.message || ...)
```
This is fine functionally, but OxLint may warn on it. Change to `_e` for consistency with the rest of the codebase.

