### 3. Login Page — `/login` Route Has No Role Context
**File:** [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/App.tsx#L85)

The `/login` route renders `<Login />` with no `role` prop, which defaults to `role="admin"`. So anyone going to `/login` directly gets the **Admin Portal** login. This is a usability and security issue — the generic `/login` path should either redirect to a role-selector page or redirect to `/login/admin`.

---

### 4. Admissions — Enroll Always Assigns `class-1`
**File:** [AdminAdmissions.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/pages/admin/AdminAdmissions.tsx#L52)

```tsx
class_id: 'class-1', // Default class placement
```

Every enrolled student is hardcoded to `class-1`. Admins need a class selector during enrollment. This will put all enrolled students in one class regardless.

---

### 5. Auth: `signOut` Always Redirects to `/login` (Not Role Login)
**File:** [auth.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/lib/supabase/auth.tsx#L106)

```tsx
navigate('/login')
```

Navigates to `/login` which defaults to the Admin login (see bug #3 above). It should navigate to `/login/${role}` so teachers and parents sign in through their own portals.

---

### 6. `ProtectedRoute` — Race Condition When Profile Not Yet Loaded
**File:** [ProtectedRoute.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/BFA/src/components/auth/ProtectedRoute.tsx#L27)

```tsx
if (portalRole && role && role !== portalRole) {
  return <Navigate to={`/${role}`} replace />
}
```

When the user first loads a protected page, `role` may still be `null` (profile fetch is async) even though `loading` is `false`. The `if (!user)` check passes (user exists), but `role` is null so the `!allowedRoles.includes(role)` check fails silently, showing the page briefly before role loads. Better to also show the spinner while `role === null && user !== null`.

